column2: The Red Guards are markists who have risen in open rebellion against the government, and, more importantly, against all of what they consider to be the reactionary trappings of the material state, and even society. In opposition to the institutions of organised religion, tradition, private ownership and family, these revolutionaries seek instead to establish a 'Dictatorship of The Common Man', the first step on the long, corpse-strewn way to the promised classless utopia of Markism.

column2: The Citizen Guard are militant liberals who have risen up in rebellion against the, real or perceived, oppressive practices of the government and the state apparatus, seeking to protect their personal liberty whatever the cost. Fighting against the tyrannical state, these revolutionaries consider themselves freedom-fighters in the true sense of the word.
